  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Chef",
  "description": "<h2>Thai Cuisine Chef</h2><p>Location: Singapore</p><p>Employment Type: Full-time</p><p>Working Hours: Split shift, including weekends and Public Holidays</p><p><u><strong>Job Responsibilities:</strong></u></p><ul><li><p>Prepare and cook a variety of authentic Thai dishes according to company standards.</p></li><li><p>Support menu execution, including selected regional Thai dishes from different parts of Thailand.</p></li><li><p>Assist in food preparation, cooking, and plating during service.</p></li><li><p>Maintain kitchen cleanliness and follow food safety and hygiene standards.</p></li><li><p>Work as part of a team to ensure smooth daily kitchen operations.</p></li><li><p>Support basic inventory control and food preparation planning.</p></li><li><p>Participate in menu improvement and new dish development when required.</p></li></ul><p><u><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></u></p><ul><li><p>Experience in cooking Thai cuisine in a professional kitchen.</p></li><li><p>Interest and willingness to learn different regional Thai cooking styles (Northern, Southern, Isaan, Central).</p></li><li><p>Able to work split shifts, weekends, and Public Holidays.</p></li><li><p>Able to work in a fast-paced kitchen environment and handle standing for long hours.</p></li><li><p>Team player with positive working attitude.</p></li><li><p>Basic communication in English for kitchen coordination.</p></li><li><p>Ability to speak Thai is an advantage.</p></li><li><p>Singaporeans or PRs only.</p></li></ul><p><u><strong>What We Offer:</strong></u></p><ul><li><p>Stable full-time employment in an established Thai food business.</p></li><li><p>Opportunity to learn and work with experienced Thai chefs.</p></li><li><p>Supportive team environment with on-the-job training.</p></li><li><p>Staff meals and benefits according to company policy.</p></li></ul>",
